# ---- Decision 019 — dev-internal artifacts live in ~/proj/devflow/agentwrit/
# (sister-folder pattern — these paths never enter any git branch of this repo).
# Two handling shapes:
#   (a) PHYSICALLY MOVED out to ~/proj/devflow/agentwrit/ — the entry here is
#       belt-and-suspenders against accidental re-creation in the repo root.
#   (b) STAYING IN PLACE but untracked — the file exists on disk so Claude Code
#       discovery walks the repo cwd and finds rules/skills, but git never tracks.
#
# Replaces the previous ADR 011 "develop stays messy / main stays clean" model,
# which assumed per-branch GitHub visibility that does not exist.

# All patterns in this block are anchored to the repo root with a leading `/`.
# Without the anchor, bare paths like `audit/` match any directory at any depth
# (including `internal/audit/` which is legitimate source code). The anchor
# limits matches to files/dirs at the repo root only, which is where internal
# artifacts and scratch files actually appear.

# Group (a) — physically moved to devflow, any re-appearance at root is a mistake
/MEMORY.md
/MEMORY_ARCHIVE.md
/FLOW.md
/TECH-DEBT.md
/COWORK_SESSION.md
/COWORK_DOCS_AUDIT.md
/.active_module
/.plans/
/adr/
/audit/

# Group (b) — stay in place for Claude Code discovery, but never tracked
/CLAUDE.md
/AGENTS.md
/.claude/
/.agents/

# ---- Decision 018 — premature legal / contribution files
# ENTERPRISE_LICENSE.md — commercial product doesn't exist yet
# CLA.md / CONTRIBUTING.md — external contributions paused (Decisions 014/016)
# All three physically moved to devflow; these entries block accidental re-add
/ENTERPRISE_LICENSE.md
/CLA.md
/CONTRIBUTING.md

# ---- Historical migration batch evidence (B0–B6)
# Physically moved to ~/proj/devflow/agentwrit/tests/ — not needed for ongoing
# development. sec-l2b kept in public tests/ because scripts/smoke/core-contract.sh
# references it. LIVE-TEST-TEMPLATE.md kept as the public process doc.
tests/app-launch-tokens/
tests/p0-production-foundations/
tests/p1-admin-secret/
tests/sec-a1/
tests/sec-l1/
tests/sec-l2a/

# Scratch / experiment files at repo root (move to devflow or delete)
/AgentWrit
/cspell.json

# M-sec gate artifacts — generated by ./scripts/gates.sh full, not checked in
coverage.out
sbom.spdx.json

# Editor-specific settings — VSCode auto-recreates settings.json with Snyk
# IDE preferences and other per-user state. Keep it out of the tree entirely.
# strip_for_main.sh and .githooks/pre-commit both enforce this for main;
# ignoring it in .gitignore prevents accidental commits on ANY branch.
.vscode/

# Credential scratch pads at the repo root — filenames containing TOKEN / SECRET /
# CREDENTIAL at the top level are assumed to be temporary holding spots for real
# secrets and must never be committed. The leading `/` anchors these patterns to
# the repo root ONLY, so legitimate source files in subdirectories (e.g.
# internal/token/, cmd/awrit/token.go, docs/credential-model.md) are not affected.
# AgentWrit is a credential broker — "token" and "credential" are central domain
# vocabulary and show up all through the source tree.
/*TOKEN*
/*SECRET*
/*CREDENTIAL*
